The script loads the parameter sweep grid data generated in Step 3. It creates a 1x3 multi-panel figure to visualize the Reheating Temperature (Trh), Spectral Index (ns), and its running (alphas) across the (Ns, H/MPl) parameter space. Panel (a) displays Trh using a logarithmic color scale. A bold red line is added at the bottom edge of the plot to indicate the direction of the off-scale BBN boundary, and an explanatory text box is included to clarify the physical validity of the 10^18 MeV scale. Panels (b) and (c) are 1D plots showing ns and alphas vs Ns for three representative values of H/MPl (10^-5, 10^-3.5, and 10^-2). The Planck 2018 constraints are overlaid as horizontal shaded bands (ns = 0.965 +/- 0.004 and alphas = -0.0045 +/- 0.0067). The script prints summary statistics and a physical explanation for the reheating temperature scale to the console. Finally, the plot is saved as a high-resolution PNG file in the data/ directory.

**Modifications:**

Converted panels (b) and (c) from 2D colormaps to 1D line plots (ns vs Ns and alphas vs Ns) for selected H/MPl slices, allowing the Planck constraints to be plotted as horizontal bands. Added a bold red line in panel (a) to represent the off-scale BBN boundary. Added an explanatory text box in panel (a) and detailed console prints to clarify that Trh ~ 10^18 MeV is the physically correct scale for instantaneous reheating in high-scale inflation. Adjusted y-axis limits in panels (b) and (c) to focus on the observationally relevant regions.

